brookfield asset management inc type public traded as tsx bama nyse bam euronext bama sptsx  component industry asset management founded  founder william mackenzie frederick stark pearson headquarters brookfield place toronto ontario canada area served global key people frank mckenna chairman bruce flatt ceo services financial services revenue  bn  operating income  million  net income  billion  aum  billion  total equity  billion  number of employees  operating employees  investment professionals  subsidiaries brookfield property partners  brookfield infrastructure partners brookfield renewable partners brookfield business partners website wwwbrookfieldcom brookfield asset management inc is a global alternative asset manager with approximately  billion of assets under management focusing on the real asset sectors of property renewable energy and infrastructure the companys corporate headquarters are located in toronto and new york city the company was founded in  as a builder and operator of electricity and transport infrastructure in brazil the companys earlier name of brascan reflected this history brasil  canada the company provided electricity and tram services in são paulo and rio de janeiro and the brazilian side after the split is still known as light short for brazilian traction light and power co ltd over the next century the company expanded and is now an investor in and operator of approximately  billion of real assets with  employees in over  offices in  different countries its major public subsidiaries include brookfield infrastructure partners brookfield renewable partners brookfield property partners and brookfield business partners contents  assets  management  history      mergers and acquisitions  birch mountain class action    launch of brookfield renewable energy partners  general growth properties  kerzner lawsuit  são paulo brazil  brookfield property partners launched  city of london acquisition  investments in brazil chile and maine    mpg office trust inc  brookfield cold storage launched  longview timber and longview fibre sales  carson block mentions brookfield in article  acquisition of industrial developments international    texas utility energy  acquisition of irish wind farms    canary wharf  acquisition of graftech north american palladium and armtec  associated estates  asciano    isagén  potsdamer platz  renaming of brookfield renewable partners lp  launch of brookfield business partners  petróleo brasileiro sa  odebrecht ambiental    greenergy fuels and maax bath  loblaw companies  see also  references  external links assetsedit the companys asset management offerings for institutional investors are focused on real assets but also include alternativetype investments structured financial products traditional fixed income and equities and finiterisk reinsurance in addition brookfield asset management owns a significant stake in a real estate services company offering home relocations property appraisals movein services and home transaction closing services and capital market services including financial advisory securities underwriting and property brokerage brookfield asset management invests through public listed companies and through private funds the companys institutional clients mainly include governments sovereign wealth funds pension plans institutions corporations and highnetworth individuals brookfield has  billion of assets under management in canada  billion invested in the united states  billion invested in asia pacific  billion in south america and  billion in the uk western europe and the middle east its major real estate investments include brookfield place formerly known as the world financial center in new york brookfield place in toronto canary wharf in london owned with qatars sovereign wealth fund potsdamer platz in berlin the bank of america plaza in los angeles bankers hall in calgary darling park in sydney and brookfield place in perth brookfields infrastructure assets include utilities electric and gas distribution transport railway and coal terminals and ports energy transmission and communications infrastructure  brookfields renewable power assets include hydroelectric power plants and wind power assets brookfield’s private equity business focuses on real assets through owning and operating in the business services industrial operations and residential development services industries managementedit j bruce flatt is senior managing partner and chief executive officer mr flatt was appointed to this position in february  after having served as chief executive officer of brookfield properties since  he was trained as an accountant at clarkson gordon and company which is now part of ernst  young as of fiscal year  his basic compensation was  million mr flatt is senior managing partner and chief executive officer of the corporation and on behalf of the corporation is the chairman and a director of ggp mr flatt previously served as a board member to fraser papers and norbord incorporated mr flatt holds a business degree from the university of manitoba historyedit edit in  the são paulo railway light and power company was founded by william mackenzie frederick stark pearson and others the word railway would later be changed to tramway in  the rio de janeiro tramway light and power company was founded by mackenzies group in  brazilian traction light and power company limited was incorporated in toronto as a public company to develop hydroelectric power operations and other utility services in brazil becoming a holding company for the two previous companies in  great lakes power company limited was incorporated to provide hydroelectric power in sault ste marie and the algoma district in ontario in  brazilian traction light and power company limited changed its name to brazilian light and power company limited in  brazilian light and power company limited changes its name to brascan limited bl in  the companys brazilian assets were trans