bsite wwwbrookfieldcom brookfield asset management inc is a global alternative asset manager with approximately  billion of assets under management focusing on the real asset sectors of property renewable energy and infrastructure the companys corporate headquarters are located in toronto and new york city the company was founded in  as a builder and operator of electricity and transport infrastructure in brazil the companys earlier name of brascan reflected this history brasil  canada the company provided electricity and tram services in são paulo and rio de janeiro and the brazilian side after the split is still known as light short for brazilian traction light and power co ltd over the next century the company expanded and is now an investor in and operator of approximately  billion of real assets with  employees in over  offices in  different countries its major public subsidiaries include brookfield infrastructure partners brookfield renewable partners brookfield property partners and brookfield business partners contents  assets  management  history      mergers and acquisitions  birch mountain class action    launch of brookfield renewable energy partners  general growth properties  kerzner lawsuit  são paulo brazil  brookfield property partners launched  city of london acquisition  investments in brazil chile and maine    mpg office trust inc  brookfield cold storage launched  longview timber and longview fibre sales  carson block mentions brookfield in article  acquisition of industrial developments international    texas utility energy  acquisition of irish wind farms    canary wharf  acquisition of graftech north american palladium and armtec  associated estates  asciano    isagén  potsdamer platz  renaming of brookfield renewable partners lp  launch of brookfield business partners  petróleo brasileiro sa  odebrecht ambiental    greenergy fuels and maax bath  loblaw companies  see also  references  external links assetsedit the companys asset management offerings for institutional investors are focused on real assets but also include alternativetype investments structured financial products traditional fixed income and equities and finiterisk reinsurance in addition brookfield asset management owns a significant stake in a real estate services company offering home relocations property appraisals movein services and home transaction closing services and capital market services including financial advisory securities underwriting and property brokerage brookfield asset management invests through public listed companies and through private funds the companys institutional clients mainly include governments sovereign wealth funds pension plans institutions corporations and highnetworth individuals brookfield has  billion of assets under management in canada  billion invested in the united states  billion invested in asia pacific  billion in south america and  billion in the uk western europe and the middle east its major real estate investments include brookfield place formerly known as the world financial center in new york brookfield place in toronto canary wharf in london owned with qatars sovereign wealth fund potsdamer platz in berlin the bank of america plaza in los angeles bankers hall in calgary darling park in sydney and brookfield place in perth brookfields infrastructure assets include utilities electric and gas distribution transport railway and coal terminals and ports energy transmission and communications infrastructure  brookfields renewable power assets include hydroelectric power plants and wind power assets brookfield’s private equity business focuses on real assets through owning and operating in the business services industrial operations and residential development services industries managementedit j bruce flatt is senior managing partner and chief executive officer mr flatt was appointed to this position in february  after having served as chief executive officer of brookfield properties since  he was trained as an accountant at clarkson gordon and company which is now part of ernst  young as of fiscal year  his basic compensation was  million mr flatt is senior managing partner and chief executive officer of the corporation and on behalf of the corporation is the chairman and a director of ggp mr flatt previously served as a board member to fraser papers and norbord incorporated mr flatt holds a business degree from the university of manitoba historyedit edit in  the são paulo railway light and power company was founded by william mackenzie frederick stark pearson and others the word railway would later be changed to tramway in  the rio de janeiro tramway light and power company was founded by mackenzies group in  brazilian traction light and power company limited was incorporated in toronto as a public company to develop hydroelectric power operations and other utility services in brazil becoming a holding company for the two previous companies in  great lakes power company limited was incorporated to provide hydroelectric power in sault ste marie and the algoma district in ontario in  brazilian traction light and power company limited changed its name to brazilian light and power company limited in  brazilian light and power company limited changes its name to brascan limited bl in  the companys brazilian assets were transferred to brazilian ownership eg eletropaulo and light sa  now aes eletropaulo the company meanwhile having diversified to other areas edit mergers and acquisitionsedit in  the company changed its name to brookfield asset management bam as part of a number of purchases in  brookfield acquired multiplex group construction company for  billion and renamed it brookfield multiplex in  the company was rebranded as multiplex it also acquired longview fibre company expanding its timberland platform to  million acres  km² in  brookfield infrastructure partners was spun out of the holding company and subsequently merged with australias prime infrastructure in a  billion transaction birch mountain class actionedit the birch mountain class action lawsuit has consistently been dismissed with judges finding in favour of brookfield and against the plaintiffs in a process supervised by the alberta courts pricewaterhousecoopers pwc was appointed receiver of birch mountain resources in november  after birch mountain had defaulted on its debts birch mountain’s assets were transferred to tricap partners ltd now operating under the hammerstone corporation a subsidiary of brookfield special situations group for approximately  million  a group called birch mountain shareholders for justice filed a lawsuit against brookfield asset management on september   with the superior court of justice in ontario canada the lawsuit challenged the acquisition and transfer of assets from a public company birch mountain resources to the hammerstone corporation the case was dismissed in its entirety after the judge ruled it had no legal merit in april  on may   the plaintiffs filed a notice of appeal in the case in mcdonald v brookfield asset management inc in the court of appeal alberta the appeal was heard on june   over the hammerstone project megaquarry in alberta on dec   the court of appeal of alberta again dismissed the case ruling that the appeal was without merit edit launch of brookfield renewable energy partnersedit in  brookfield renewable energy partners was launched as an exchangelisted global renewable power company with a portfolio of hydroelectric and wind power plants in canada the united states and brazil general growth propertiesedit also in  brookfield led a successful restructuring of general growth properties the second largest owner of us shopping malls out of bankruptcy after rebuffing simon property groups attempt to acquire ggp in  the company increased its share of general growth properties to  by  brookfields stake in ggp grew to  which prompted investor activist william ackman to request that ggp create a special committee unaffiliated with brookfield to consider a sale to simon on dec   pershing square agreed to sell a portfolio of its stake in ggp to brookfield and struck a fouryear agreement to be a passive investor in the shopping mall company by may  pershing square had sold all of its shares in ggp kerzner lawsuitedit in january  two hedge fund creditors trilogy portfolio co and canyon value realization fund lp in a loan with brookfield filed a lawsuit in delaware chancery court in wilmington asking that the court restrain brookfields attempt to acquire the kerzner international properties from closing in the lawsuit the hedge funds alleged that brookfield engaged in brazen selfdealing and collusion with junior lender pccp and servicer wells fargo to complete the deal in violation of the loan agreement the court granted a temporary injunction pending a hearing brookfield consequently cancelled its offer to acquire the property brookfield walked away after a delaware judge issued the injunction the two hedge funds subsequently agreed to a restructuring that allowed brookfield to acquire the oneonly ocean club in the bahamas atlantis paradise island resort in the bahamas and the oneonly palmilla resort in mexico brookfield subsequently sold the one  only ocean club to access industries for  million são paulo braziledit in  brazilian authorities announced that they were investigating allegations that an executive at brookfield bribed são paulo building officials to secure permits required for renovating three shopping malls the allegations were made by daniela gonzalez the former chief financial officer of a brookfield subsidiary in brazil who was fired by brookfield in  the alleged bribes reportedly totaled  silvio antonio marques a são paulo state prosecutor confirmed the civil and criminal investigations to the wall street journal and added that the reporting individual also provided documentation of the misconduct by brookfield employees a former brookfield employee who is being sued by brookfield for embezzlement and is being investigated by brazilian authorities reported the alleged bribes to both the authorities in brazil and to the us securities and exchange commission brazilian authorities say they are questioning a company controlled by brookfield asset management as part of an investigation into allegations that são paulo officials engaged in extortion in the continuing sec inquiry the agency has been looking into allegations made by a former brookfield executive who says she was ordered to bribe city officials to obtain permits required for shopping malls and says she was fired for refusing to do so in june  the securities and exchange commission informed brookfield asset management that it had concluded its investigation and would not be bringing charges over alleged bribery in brazil brookfield property partners launchededit in  the company announced plans to spin off its global property holdings to shareholders in brookfield asset management by distributing units in a new entity brookfield property partners city of london acquisitionedit in june  brookfield office properties announced plans to acquire a portfolio of three office buildings and a development site in the city of london for  million from hammerson inc a british real estate company focused on retail developments investments in brazil chile and maineedit in july  brookfield and spanish toll road operator abertis announced plans to acquire a toll road network in brazil at the same time brookfield acquired full control of toll road assets in chile in december  brookfield renewable energy partners agreed to acquire a portfolio of  hydroelectric power stations in maine from nextera energy resources llc for  million edit mpg office trust incedit on april   brookfield office properties made an offer for mpg office trust inc and announced plans to create a new  billion fund that would hold seven mpg and brookfield office buildings in los angeles brookfield cold storage launchededit in june  a brookfield private equity fund acquired two canadian refrigeration facilities in toronto and calgary from millard refrigerated services launching a new national company brookfield cold storage longview timber and longview fibre salesedit in june  brookfield also announced two separate transactions totaling  billion that saw the sale of its longview timber unit to weyerhauser for  billion and the sale of longview fibre paper and packaging to kapstone paper and packaging for  billion brookfield purchased the companies in  with  billion of equity in commenting on the transaction kapstone chairman and ceo roger stone said the longview team orchestrated a transformation that is truly in my experience the most amazing that ive actually ever seen in my  years in the industry carson block mentions brookfield in articleedit in july  the new york times ran an article by short seller carson block of muddy waters lcc that cited brookfield as one of a number of companies that had miscalculated the risks of investing in brazil acquisition of industrial developments internationaledit in august  brookfield property partners acquired industrial developments international an atlantabased owner of distribution facilities from japanese construction company kajima corp in a  billion transaction edit texas utility energyedit brookfield was revealed to be a significant creditor in an arm of bankrupt texas utility energy future holdings as a holder of debt in the company’s texas competitive electric holdings subsidiary acquisition of irish wind farmsedit in march  brookfield renewable energy acquired a portfolio of irish wind farms for  million as part of a privatization by the irish government edit canary wharfedit brookfield property partners and the qatar investment authority acquired the parent to the canary wharf real estate development in london for ₤ billion brookfield was the biggest buyer of european real estate in  acquisition of graftech north american palladium and armtecedit brookfield’s private equity arm brookfield capital partners acquired a number of industrial companies including graftech international north american palladium and armtec associated estatesedit brookfield property partners acquired apartment owner associated estates for  billion after the company put itself up for sale ascianoedit in august  brookfield infrastructure bid approximately  billion for australian rail port and logistics company asciano edit isagénedit on january   brookfield acquired  of the power generation company isagén in colombia for a sum of  trillion cop  billion usd the company subsequently increased its interest to  by the end of the year potsdamer platzedit in early  brookfield announced that it partnered with korea investment corp to purchase a major chunk of potsdamer platz in berlin acquiring a total of  buildings the total acquisition price was  billion in announcing the transaction brookfield property partners chairman ric clark said the company is looking for additional world class assets renaming of brookfield renewable partners lpedit on may   brookfield renewable energy partners lp changed its name to brookfield renewable partners lp the stock symbol tsx bepun  nyse bep and cusip remained the same launch of brookfield business partnersedit in june  brookfield completed the spinoff of brookfield business partners the primary public vehicle through which brookfield will own and operate the business services and industrial operations of its private equity group petróleo brasileiro saedit brookfield infrastructure announced in september that together with its investment partners they would acquire a  percent stake in a brazilian natural gas pipeline from petróleo brasileiro sa odebrecht ambientaledit in october brookfield business partners and its institutional partners bought a  percent stake in the largest private water and sewage company in brazil odebrecht ambiental in a transaction valued at  million under its new ownership the business was renamed brk ambiental  edit greenergy fuels and maax bathedit brookfield business partners and its institutional partners agreed to acquire a  percent controlling stake in greenergy fuels holdings ltd  a leading provider of road fuels in the uk the company also reached an agreement to sell maax bath a bathroomfixtures company to american bath group loblaw companiesedit in april  the company announced an agreement to purchase  of the gas station operations of loblaw companies canada’s largest retailer see alsoedit toronto portal companies portal edper investments the bronfman holding company that controlled brascan from  list of real estate companies of canada referencesedit  a b c d e brookfield asset management reports  results pdf brookfield asset management  march  retrieved  may    schedule da us securities and exchange commission retrieved december     bloomberg markets bloombergcom retrieved    contact brookfield  brookfield properties wwwbrookfieldpropertiescom retrieved    won shirley september   whats in a name plenty if its brascan the globe and mail   brazilian traction light and power company ltd bloomberg lp retrieved december     a b brookfield asset management inc  annual report pdf retrieved  may    brookfield asset management inc  annual report pdf  march  retrieved  may    brookfield asset profit weaken revenue increases toronto the globe and mail february     brookfield asset management stock quote toronto the globe and mail february   retrieved december     pachner joannabrookfield asset management a perfect predatorcanadian business canada august retrieved september  brookfield asset mgmt looks to emerging markets reuters november     brookfield moves to simplify structure of its north american property arm the globe and mail retrieved    sectors  brookfield asset management wwwbrookfieldcom retrieved    bank of america plaza   south hope street los angeles  brookfield properties wwwbrookfieldproperti